race.comment: Doesn't look too many win chances. RUSSIAN ROYALTY (11) might be over the odds here. Looked close to a win two and three starts back with two good runs then was below best last time at Warrnambool. This is easier and well worth another chance. Best figures measure up. GOOD LORDY ME (2) will go off as favourite after a string of minor placings, the latest trying to lead throughout over a similar trip at Mornington. Overdue and sure to take catching. SASTERION (3) has been edging towards a win, the latest finishing fourth over 1800m at Horsham. Looks suited by the extra ground and fitter. FIORENTE RULES (6) has been midfield at both starts so far but has the blinkers added and looks well suited by the extra ground. Could improve sharply. HEART'S EMBRACE (7) was thereabouts last time and can do much better.
